h a series of in-depth interviews, she also draws on the memories of people with direct experience of Soviet housing and domestic life. Attwood has produced not just a history of housing, but a social history of daily life which will appeal both to scholars and those with a general interest in Soviet history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aSoviet history.  aSoviet housing.  adomestic life.  adomestic space.  agender relations.  ahistory of housing.  ahome life.  ahousing policy.  ahousing shortage.  asocialism.1 aAttwood, Lynne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779263140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847792631423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847792631/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles